{
  "texts": [
    "[77] 2022 Email Writing \"AI hallucination\" refers to factually incorrect or nonexistent content generated by the LLM. 47 Gehrmann et al.",
    "[78] 2022 Natural Language Generation \"AI hallucination\" refers to a situation where a model is not faithful as it adds information not present in the source document.",
    "\"Intrinsic hallucinations\" misrepresent facts in the input.",
    "\"Extrinsic hallucinations\" ignore the input altogether. 48 Erdem et al.",
    "[79] 2022 Natural Language Generation \"AI hallucination\" refers to the generation of descriptions or facts that are not fully supported by the input. 49 Tun et al."
  ]
}